.TH ZSH-MANAGER 1 "2026-04-19" "v2.3" "SafeITExperts — zsh-manager"
.SH NAME
zsh-manager \- unified dispatcher for btrfs snapshot and filesystem management on openSUSE Tumbleweed
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B snap-man
.br
.B snap-help
.br
.B snap-del
.RI [ id ]
.br
.B snap-compare
.I id1 id2
.br
.B snap-important
.br
.B snap-manual
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B zsh-manager
is an Oh My Zsh hub plugin providing a unified dispatcher menu and shared commands for btrfs/snapper management on openSUSE Tumbleweed.
It coordinates the following independent plugins:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B zsh-snap-new
\(em guided snapshot creation
.IP \(bu 2
.B zsh-snap-list
\(em colorized snapshot listing
.IP \(bu 2
.B zsh-snap-rollback
\(em interactive rollback
.IP \(bu 2
.B zsh-btrfs-scrub
\(em btrfs scrub management
.IP \(bu 2
.B zsh-btrfs-balance
\(em btrfs balance management
.IP \(bu 2
.B zsh-btrfs-health
\(em btrfs health report
.RE
.PP
If a plugin is not loaded, stub functions display an install hint rather than failing silently.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B snap-man
Open the unified interactive dispatcher menu. Shortcuts: \fBman-s\fR.
.TP
.B snap-help
List all available commands across the hub and its plugins. Shortcut: \fBsnap-h\fR.
.TP
.BI snap-del " id"
Delete snapshot by ID. Displays the snapshot list if no ID is given.
Shortcut: \fBsnap-d\fR.
.TP
.BI snap-compare " id1 id2"
Show files changed between two snapshots using \fBsnapper diff\fR.
Shortcut: \fBsnap-c\fR.
.TP
.B snap-important
Display only snapshots marked \fBimportant=yes\fR.
.TP
.B snap-manual
Display only manually created snapshots (excludes zypper and timeline entries).
.SH ALIASES
.SS Short aliases
.TP
.B man-s
snap-man
.TP
.B snap-l
snap-list (via zsh-snap-list)
.TP
.B snap-n
snap-new (via zsh-snap-new)
.TP
.B snap-r
snap-rollback (via zsh-snap-rollback)
.TP
.B snap-d
snap-del
.TP
.B snap-c
snap-compare
.TP
.B snap-h
snap-help
.SS Multi-config aliases
.TP
.B snap-list-root
sudo snapper -c root list
.TP
.B snap-list-home
sudo snapper -c home list
.TP
.B snap-create-root
sudo snapper -c root create --description
.TP
.B snap-create-home
sudo snapper -c home create --description
.TP
.B snap-cleanup
sudo snapper cleanup number
.TP
.B snap-cleanup-all
sudo snapper cleanup all
.TP
.B rollback-last
sudo snapper rollback (no confirmation — expert use)
.SH STUBS
If a plugin is not installed, its function is replaced by a stub that prints an install hint:
.RS
snap-list, snap-new, snap-rollback, btrfs-scrub, btrfs-balance, btrfs-balance-threshold, btrfs-snap-size, btrfs-health
.RE
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.IP \(bu 2
openSUSE Tumbleweed
.IP \(bu 2
zsh 5.9+
.IP \(bu 2
Oh My Zsh
.IP \(bu 2
snapper \(em sudo zypper install snapper
.IP \(bu 2
btrfs-progs \(em sudo zypper install btrfs-progs
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.oh-my-zsh/custom/plugins/zsh-manager/zsh-manager.plugin.zsh
Plugin file (crisis user)
.TP
.I /root/.oh-my-zsh/custom/plugins/zsh-manager/zsh-manager.plugin.zsh
Plugin file (root)
